The paper deals with a computational problem related to string mapping, which is a topic in computer science that falls under several sub-categories. The use of the color-coding technique suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The problem also involves the conservation of duos, which is a combinatorial aspect that could place the paper in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The kernelization result and the use of algorithms suggest that the paper may also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The problem involves mapping strings, which could place the paper in the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. Finally, the problem involves finding a maximum, which could place the paper in the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
